<subSubSection id="C3776556ED2A384EFF78FD47FE79FD26" pageId="635" pageNumber="636" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED2A384EFF78FD47FE79FD26" blockId="635.[136,778,479,2070]" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED2A384EFF78FD47FEFBFD62" bold="true" box="[189,318,649,675]" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific name is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED2A384EFF14FD62FF3BFD04" box="[209,254,684,709]" italics="true" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">scut</emphasis>
(=a shield) and refers to the shield-shaped rostrum of the new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED2A384EFF78FD21FEBBF84F" pageId="635" pageNumber="636" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED2A384EFF78FD21FE30FB02" blockId="635.[136,778,479,2070]" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED2A384EFF78FD21FE29FCC8" bold="true" box="[189,492,751,777]" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">Description of female</emphasis>
. Body (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED2A384EFDB3FD21FCC7FCC8" box="[630,770,751,777]" captionStart="FIGURE 431" captionStartId="636.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[211,1353,216,1849]" captionTargetId="figure-19@636.[207,1381,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="636" captionText="FIGURE 431. Nodoscarus scutatus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, cephalosome, right; C, cephalosome, dorsal; D, posterior end of body, ventrolateral; E, caudal ramus; F, cephalosome, ventral; G, rostrum; H, antennule; I, antenna; J, labrum and mouthparts in situ. Scale bars: A. 0.5 mm; B–D, F, G, 0.1 mm; E, I, 0.02 mm; H, J, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592182/files/figure.png" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">Fig. 431A</figureCitation>
) vermiform, elongate, unsegmented, and curved. Body length 5.23 mm; body width 0.63 mm across widest region in middle. Cephalosome (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED2A384EFDC2FC9BFD66FCAE" box="[519,675,853,879]" captionStart="FIGURE 431" captionStartId="636.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[211,1353,216,1849]" captionTargetId="figure-19@636.[207,1381,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="636" captionText="FIGURE 431. Nodoscarus scutatus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, cephalosome, right; C, cephalosome, dorsal; D, posterior end of body, ventrolateral; E, caudal ramus; F, cephalosome, ventral; G, rostrum; H, antennule; I, antenna; J, labrum and mouthparts in situ. Scale bars: A. 0.5 mm; B–D, F, G, 0.1 mm; E, I, 0.02 mm; H, J, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592182/files/figure.png" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">Fig. 431B, C</figureCitation>
) defined from metasome by margins of cephalic shield, narrower than metasome. Posterior part of body bearing copulatory pore on ventral surface (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED2A384EFE59FC75FDD4FC14" box="[412,529,955,981]" captionStart="FIGURE 431" captionStartId="636.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[211,1353,216,1849]" captionTargetId="figure-19@636.[207,1381,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="636" captionText="FIGURE 431. Nodoscarus scutatus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, cephalosome, right; C, cephalosome, dorsal; D, posterior end of body, ventrolateral; E, caudal ramus; F, cephalosome, ventral; G, rostrum; H, antennule; I, antenna; J, labrum and mouthparts in situ. Scale bars: A. 0.5 mm; B–D, F, G, 0.1 mm; E, I, 0.02 mm; H, J, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592182/files/figure.png" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">Fig. 431D</figureCitation>
) and short, transverse dorsal slit (posterior part of body in 
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED2A384EFDE0FC13FD53FC36" box="[549,662,989,1015]" captionStart="FIGURE 431" captionStartId="636.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[211,1353,216,1849]" captionTargetId="figure-19@636.[207,1381,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="636" captionText="FIGURE 431. Nodoscarus scutatus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, cephalosome, right; C, cephalosome, dorsal; D, posterior end of body, ventrolateral; E, caudal ramus; F, cephalosome, ventral; G, rostrum; H, antennule; I, antenna; J, labrum and mouthparts in situ. Scale bars: A. 0.5 mm; B–D, F, G, 0.1 mm; E, I, 0.02 mm; H, J, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592182/files/figure.png" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">Fig. 431A</figureCitation>
distorted) representing vestige of articulation between prosome and urosome. Caudal rami (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED2A384EFE5AFBEFFDF8FBFD" box="[415,573,1057,1084]" captionStart="FIGURE 431" captionStartId="636.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[211,1353,216,1849]" captionTargetId="figure-19@636.[207,1381,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="636" captionText="FIGURE 431. Nodoscarus scutatus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, cephalosome, right; C, cephalosome, dorsal; D, posterior end of body, ventrolateral; E, caudal ramus; F, cephalosome, ventral; G, rostrum; H, antennule; I, antenna; J, labrum and mouthparts in situ. Scale bars: A. 0.5 mm; B–D, F, G, 0.1 mm; E, I, 0.02 mm; H, J, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592182/files/figure.png" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">Fig. 431D, E</figureCitation>
) present, slightly longerthan wide (43×38 μm), incompletely articulated from abdomen, graduallynarrowing distally; armedwith 6 unequal caudal setae, all shorter than width of ramus at base, proximalmost seta longest.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED2A384EFF78FB02FD1EF9D6" blockId="635.[136,778,479,2070]" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">
Rostrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED2A384EFEEAFB05FE0CFB27" box="[303,457,1227,1254]" captionStart="FIGURE 431" captionStartId="636.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[211,1353,216,1849]" captionTargetId="figure-19@636.[207,1381,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="636" captionText="FIGURE 431. Nodoscarus scutatus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, cephalosome, right; C, cephalosome, dorsal; D, posterior end of body, ventrolateral; E, caudal ramus; F, cephalosome, ventral; G, rostrum; H, antennule; I, antenna; J, labrum and mouthparts in situ. Scale bars: A. 0.5 mm; B–D, F, G, 0.1 mm; E, I, 0.02 mm; H, J, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592182/files/figure.png" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">Fig. 431G, H</figureCitation>
) large, shield-shaped, about twice as long as wide (231×119 μm), widest in middle; lateral margins parallel in proximal third, tapering and setulose in distal two-thirds.Antennule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED2A384EFD83FAFFFD7CFA8A" box="[582,697,1329,1355]" captionStart="FIGURE 431" captionStartId="636.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[211,1353,216,1849]" captionTargetId="figure-19@636.[207,1381,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="636" captionText="FIGURE 431. Nodoscarus scutatus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, cephalosome, right; C, cephalosome, dorsal; D, posterior end of body, ventrolateral; E, caudal ramus; F, cephalosome, ventral; G, rostrum; H, antennule; I, antenna; J, labrum and mouthparts in situ. Scale bars: A. 0.5 mm; B–D, F, G, 0.1 mm; E, I, 0.02 mm; H, J, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592182/files/figure.png" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">Fig. 431H</figureCitation>
) small, lobate, subcircular, with mix of setae and setules on distal and posterior surfaces. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED2A384EFE3FFABBFDA6FA51" box="[506,611,1397,1424]" captionStart="FIGURE 431" captionStartId="636.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[211,1353,216,1849]" captionTargetId="figure-19@636.[207,1381,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="636" captionText="FIGURE 431. Nodoscarus scutatus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, cephalosome, right; C, cephalosome, dorsal; D, posterior end of body, ventrolateral; E, caudal ramus; F, cephalosome, ventral; G, rostrum; H, antennule; I, antenna; J, labrum and mouthparts in situ. Scale bars: A. 0.5 mm; B–D, F, G, 0.1 mm; E, I, 0.02 mm; H, J, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592182/files/figure.png" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">Fig. 431I</figureCitation>
) 3-segmented; coxa and basis unarmed; unsegmented endopod about 3.7 times longer than wide (62×17 μm), slightly shorter than basis: armedwith 7 setae (arranged as 3, 2, and 2) plus slender terminal claw, about half as long as endopod.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED2A384EFF78F9D1FDEDF8AD" blockId="635.[136,778,479,2070]" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">
Labrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED2A384EFEE7F9D1FE4CF9FB" box="[290,393,1567,1594]" captionStart="FIGURE 431" captionStartId="636.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[211,1353,216,1849]" captionTargetId="figure-19@636.[207,1381,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="636" captionText="FIGURE 431. Nodoscarus scutatus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, cephalosome, right; C, cephalosome, dorsal; D, posterior end of body, ventrolateral; E, caudal ramus; F, cephalosome, ventral; G, rostrum; H, antennule; I, antenna; J, labrum and mouthparts in situ. Scale bars: A. 0.5 mm; B–D, F, G, 0.1 mm; E, I, 0.02 mm; H, J, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592182/files/figure.png" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">Fig.431J</figureCitation>
) rather large, smooth, withrounded posterior margin. Mandible (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED2A384EFE2BF98FFDAAF99D" box="[494,623,1601,1628]" captionStart="FIGURE 432" captionStartId="637.[136,245,819,845]" captionTargetBox="[161,1433,241,748]" captionTargetId="figure-18@637.[136,1451,223,758]" captionTargetPageId="637" captionText="FIGURE 432. Nodoscarus scutatus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, mandible; B, maxillule; C, maxilla. Scale bars: 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592184" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592184/files/figure.png" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">Fig. 432A</figureCitation>
) represented by biramous palp, armed with 4 setae on outer ramus (exopod) and 5 setae on inner ramus (endopod). Maxillule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED2A384EFF55F969FEC7F903" box="[144,258,1703,1730]" captionStart="FIGURE 432" captionStartId="637.[136,245,819,845]" captionTargetBox="[161,1433,241,748]" captionTargetId="figure-18@637.[136,1451,223,758]" captionTargetPageId="637" captionText="FIGURE 432. Nodoscarus scutatus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, mandible; B, maxillule; C, maxilla. Scale bars: 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592184" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592184/files/figure.png" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">Fig. 432B</figureCitation>
) as unsegmented lobe, fan-like and armed with 9 broad setae, 2 on medial margin smaller than others. Maxilla (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED2A384EFF39F925FEBEF8C7" box="[252,379,1771,1798]" captionStart="FIGURE 432" captionStartId="637.[136,245,819,845]" captionTargetBox="[161,1433,241,748]" captionTargetId="figure-18@637.[136,1451,223,758]" captionTargetPageId="637" captionText="FIGURE 432. Nodoscarus scutatus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, mandible; B, maxillule; C, maxilla. Scale bars: 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592184" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592184/files/figure.png" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">Fig. 432C</figureCitation>
) incompletely 3-segmented and armed with 4, 1, and 3 setae on first to third segments, respectively. All setae on mandible, maxillule and maxilla pinnate. Maxillipeds and legs absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED2A384EFF78F8BAFEBBF84F" blockId="635.[136,778,479,2070]" box="[189,382,1908,1934]" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED2A384EFF78F8BAFF3FF84F" bold="true" box="[189,250,1908,1934]" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">Male</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED2A384EFF78F858FB58FD9E" pageId="635" pageNumber="636" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED2A384EFF78F858FAF7FE74" blockId="635.[136,778,479,2070]" lastBlockId="635.[810,1452,173,607]" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED2A384EFF78F858FEEFF871" bold="true" box="[189,298,1942,1968]" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">Remarks</emphasis>
. The maxilla of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED2A384EFE1BF858FD9CF86E" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[478,601,1942,1968]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Nodoscarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="635" pageNumber="636" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scutatus" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED2A384EFE1BF858FE34F86E" box="[478,497,1942,1967]" italics="true" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED2A384EFE38F858FD9CF86E" box="[509,601,1942,1967]" italics="true" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">scutatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED2A384EFD9BF858FCCFF871" box="[606,778,1942,1968]" pageId="635" pageNumber="636" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED2A384EFD9BF858FCC6F871" bold="true" box="[606,771,1942,1968]" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">gen. et sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is 3-segmented and armed with 4, 1, and 3 setae on the firsttothird segments, respectively, asin 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED2A384EFD9AF814FD14F835" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[607,721,2010,2036]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Nodoscarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="635" pageNumber="636" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bretoni" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED2A384EFD9AF814FDB7F832" box="[607,626,2010,2035]" italics="true" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED2A384EFD44F814FD14F835" box="[641,721,2010,2036]" italics="true" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">bretoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFED2A384EFD1CF814FEC5F7D7" bold="true" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED2A384EFD1CF814FEC5F7D7" pageId="635" pageNumber="636" rank="species">gen. etsp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
However, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED2A384EFE41F832FDC4F7D4" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[388,513,2044,2070]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Nodoscarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="635" pageNumber="636" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scutatus" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED2A384EFE41F832FE52F7D4" box="[388,407,2044,2069]" italics="true" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED2A384EFE60F832FDC4F7D4" box="[421,513,2044,2069]" italics="true" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">scutatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFED2A384EFDCCF832FD7CF7D7" bold="true" box="[521,697,2044,2070]" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED2A384EFDCCF832FD7CF7D7" box="[521,697,2044,2070]" pageId="635" pageNumber="636" rank="species">gen. etsp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs in the possession of defined caudal rami, in the presence of 9 setae on the mandible (vs. 10 setae in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED2A384EFAC6FF1EFAB1FF28" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[1283,1396,207,233]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Nodoscarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="635" pageNumber="636" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bretoni" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED2A384EFAC6FF1EFAD3FF28" box="[1283,1302,208,233]" italics="true" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED2A384EFAE1FF01FAB1FF28" box="[1316,1396,207,233]" italics="true" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">bretoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFED2A384EFABFFF01FC67FECA" bold="true" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED2A384EFABFFF01FC67FECA" pageId="635" pageNumber="636" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
), and of 9 setae on the maxillule (vs. 10 setae in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED2A384EFC83FEDAFC73FEEC" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[838,950,275,301]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Nodoscarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="635" pageNumber="636" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bretoni" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED2A384EFC83FEDAFC9CFEEC" box="[838,857,276,301]" italics="true" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED2A384EFCA3FEDDFC73FEEC" box="[870,950,275,301]" italics="true" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">bretoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED2A384EFC79FEDDFBA2FEEC" box="[956,1127,275,301]" pageId="635" pageNumber="636" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED2A384EFC79FEDDFBA6FEEC" bold="true" box="[956,1123,275,301]" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">gen. et sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
). As an additional difference between the two species, the antennule of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED2A384EFAC6FEF8FAB6FE8E" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[1283,1395,309,335]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Nodoscarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="635" pageNumber="636" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bretoni" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED2A384EFAC6FEF8FAD3FE8E" box="[1283,1302,310,335]" italics="true" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED2A384EFAE6FEFBFAB6FE8E" box="[1315,1395,309,335]" italics="true" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">bretoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFED2A384EFABFFEFBFC58FEB0" bold="true" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED2A384EFABFFEFBFC58FEB0" pageId="635" pageNumber="636" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is strongly tapering and has partial articulations dorsally, whereas that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED2A384EFB8BFEB4FB0BFE52" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[1102,1230,377,403]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Nodoscarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="635" pageNumber="636" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scutatus" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED2A384EFB8BFEB4FBA4FE52" box="[1102,1121,378,403]" italics="true" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED2A384EFBB7FEB4FB0BFE52" box="[1138,1230,378,403]" italics="true" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">scutatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFED2A384EFB12FEB7FA4AFE52" bold="true" box="[1239,1423,377,403]" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED2A384EFB12FEB7FA4AFE52" box="[1239,1423,377,403]" pageId="635" pageNumber="636" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is globular and lacks any trace of an articulation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED2A384EFC9AFE73FB58FD9E" blockId="635.[810,1452,173,607]" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">
It is notable that 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED2A384EFBE5FE70FB5BFE16" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[1056,1182,445,471]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Nodoscarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="635" pageNumber="636" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scutatus" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED2A384EFBE5FE70FBF6FE16" box="[1056,1075,446,471]" italics="true" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED2A384EFB87FE70FB5BFE16" box="[1090,1182,446,471]" italics="true" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">scutatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFED2A384EFB63FE73FA9CFE16" bold="true" box="[1190,1369,445,471]" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED2A384EFB63FE73FA9CFE16" box="[1190,1369,445,471]" pageId="635" pageNumber="636" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED2A384EFA57FE70FCB0FE38" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Nodoscarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="635" pageNumber="636" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curvus" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED2A384EFA57FE70FA60FE16" box="[1426,1445,446,471]" italics="true" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED2A384EFCEFFE2EFCB0FE38" box="[810,885,480,505]" italics="true" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">curvus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFED2A384EFCBEFE11FBEDFE38" bold="true" box="[891,1064,479,505]" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED2A384EFCBEFE11FBEDFE38" box="[891,1064,479,505]" pageId="635" pageNumber="636" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
share the same species of ascidian host, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED2A384EFCACFDCFFBF1FDDA" authorityName="Savigny" authorityYear="1816" box="[873,1076,513,539]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Polyclinidae" genus="Aplidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enterogona" pageId="635" pageNumber="636" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lobatum">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED2A384EFCACFDCFFBF1FDDA" box="[873,1076,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">Aplidium lobatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the former copepod species was collected from 
<collectingCountry id="F37A764DED2A384EFBC3FDEAFB73FDFC" box="[1030,1206,547,574]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
, while the latter came from off 
<collectingCountry id="F37A764DED2A384EFC4BFD8BFC2EFD9E" box="[910,1003,581,607]" name="Djibouti" pageId="635" pageNumber="636">Djibouti</collectingCountry>
in the Red Sea.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
